<Layout 
  title="Pension Planning | Financial Management"
  description="Expert guidance on pension planning for UK veterans. Understand your Armed Forces pension, civilian pension options, and how to maximise your retirement income.">
  <div class="container my-5">
    <h1 class="display-4 mb-4">Pension Planning for Veterans</h1>
    <div class="row g-4">
      <div class="col-lg-8">
        <p class="lead">Effective pension planning is crucial for ensuring financial security in retirement. This page provides guidance on understanding and maximising your pension benefits, including Armed Forces pensions and civilian options.</p>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Understanding Your Armed Forces Pension</h2>
        <p>Key points about Armed Forces pensions:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Different schemes exist depending on when you joined the Armed Forces</li>
          <li>Your pension may include a lump sum and regular payments</li>
          <li>The amount depends on factors like length of service and rank</li>
          <li>Some pensions are payable immediately upon leaving service</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Civilian Pension Options</h2>
        <p>As you transition to civilian life, consider these pension options:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Workplace pensions offered by your new employer</li>
          <li>Personal pensions you can set up independently</li>
          <li>The State Pension, which you may be eligible for alongside other pensions</li>
          <li>Self-Invested Personal Pensions (SIPPs) for more control over investments</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Maximising Your Pension</h2>
        <p>Strategies to enhance your pension income:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Start planning early and contribute regularly</li>
          <li>Consider making additional voluntary contributions</li>
          <li>Understand the tax relief available on pension contributions</li>
          <li>Review and adjust your pension investments periodically</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Pension Transfers</h2>
        <p>Points to consider about pension transfers:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>You may be able to transfer your Armed Forces pension to a civilian scheme</li>
          <li>Carefully evaluate the benefits and drawbacks of transferring</li>
          <li>Seek professional advice before making any transfer decisions</li>
          <li>Be aware of potential scams targeting pension transfers</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="h3 mt-4">Retirement Planning</h2>
        <p>Additional retirement planning considerations:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Estimate your retirement income needs</li>
          <li>Consider your desired retirement age and lifestyle</li>
          <li>Factor in potential care costs in later life</li>
          <li>Explore options for phased retirement or part-time work</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="col-lg-4">
        <div class="card bg-light mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Related Information</h3>
            <ul class="list-unstyled">
              <li><a href="/financial/budgeting" class="text-decoration-none">Budgeting Advice</a></li>
              <li><a href="/financial/investments" class="text-decoration-none">Investment Strategies</a></li>
              <li><a href="/support/financial-advice" class="text-decoration-none">Financial Advice Services</a></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card mb-4">
          <div class="card-body">
            <h3 class="h5">Pension Calculator</h3>
            <p>Use our pension calculator to estimate your retirement income and plan for your future.</p>
            <a href="/pension-calculator" class="btn btn-primary">Calculate Now</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
